I know that most inexperienced players think that pawn structure is very critical, which is untrue. The order of advantages from the highest to least in a position evaluation are: material, piece activity, king safety, and finally pawn structure. Also, here, if he takes, I get an open b file and get to exploit the weak dark squares easily. If his king castle on either side, I will have play against it.
it was probably better to keep the bishop to watch the dark squares.
